{"TopicId":186560,"ForumId":44,"TopicTitle":"[New] Space Launch System / Orion Discussion Thread","CreatedByName":"ZooNamedGames","CreatedById":103726,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-07-21T02:48:55Z","PageNum":78,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"StrandedonEarth","CreatedById":89439,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-11-03T16:07:12Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nConsensus in that Twitter thread is that the \u003Cabbr title=\u00221. Original Post(er). The first post in a thread, or the person who posted it. 2. Overpowered. A part or mechanic that upsets game balance by being too powerful.\u0022\u003EOP\u003C/abbr\u003E is a troll account\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"tater","CreatedById":119411,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-11-03T17:27:13Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224050759\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022186560\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221635955632\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002289439\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022StrandedonEarth\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, StrandedonEarth said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nConsensus in that Twitter thread is that the \u003Cabbr title=\u00221. Original Post(er). The first post in a thread, or the person who posted it. 2. Overpowered. A part or mechanic that upsets game balance by being too powerful.\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u00221. Original Post(er). The first post in a thread, or the person who posted it. 2. Overpowered. A part or mechanic that upsets game balance by being too powerful.\u0022\u003EOP\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E is a troll account\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCould well be. Hopefully so, they need to light that candle, finally.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt might also be that some minor issue was found, and rumors spun it into something it wasn\u0027t.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf I get a clear answer, I\u0027ll post it.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"tater","CreatedById":119411,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-11-03T17:52:32Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedOther\u0022\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed9075442328\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?app=core\u0026amp;module=system\u0026amp;controller=embed\u0026amp;url=https://twitter.com/JimFree/status/1455954576947957762?s=20\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"RCgothic","CreatedById":132560,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-11-04T21:57:49Z","Content":"\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedOther\u0022\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed4697256157\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?app=core\u0026amp;module=system\u0026amp;controller=embed\u0026amp;url=https://twitter.com/ChrisG_NSF/status/1456350883336396804?s=20\u0022 style=\u0022height:592px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Entropian","CreatedById":205453,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-11-05T14:41:47Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u0022Budgetary shortfalls,\u0022 hah.\u00A0 Nobody saw \u003Cem\u003Ethat\u003C/em\u003E coming...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"tater","CreatedById":119411,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-11-15T17:55:22Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u0022Artemis\u0022 but really, \u0022SLS/Orion.\u0022\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedOther\u0022\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed6548967260\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?app=core\u0026amp;module=system\u0026amp;controller=embed\u0026amp;url=https://twitter.com/NASAOIG/status/1460267931095470080?ref_src=twsrc%255Etfw%257Ctwcamp%255Etweetembed%257Ctwterm%255E1460267931095470080%257Ctwgr%255E%257Ctwcon%255Es1_c10%26ref_url=https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?app=coremodule=systemcontroller=embedurl=https://twitter.com/NASAOIG/status/1460267931095470080?s=20\u0022 style=\u0022height:283px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHas all the Artemis stuff, but you can pull out SLS costs.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Beccab","CreatedById":208000,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-11-15T18:00:37Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224055413\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022186560\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221636998922\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022119411\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022tater\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n4 minutes ago, tater said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u0022Artemis\u0022 but really, \u0022SLS/Orion.\u0022\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedOther\u0022\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed3360977563\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?app=core\u0026amp;module=system\u0026amp;controller=embed\u0026amp;url=https://twitter.com/NASAOIG/status/1460267931095470080?ref_src=twsrc%255Etfw%257Ctwcamp%255Etweetembed%257Ctwterm%255E1460267931095470080%257Ctwgr%255E%257Ctwcon%255Es1_c10%26ref_url=https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?app=coremodule=systemcontroller=embedurl=https://twitter.com/NASAOIG/status/1460267931095470080?s=20\u0022 style=\u0022height:282px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHas all the Artemis stuff, but you can pull out SLS costs.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMost important parts:\u003Cbr\u003E\n- Artemis I to happen NET summer 2022\u003Cbr\u003E\n- The initial four SLS flights to cost 4.1 billions, of which 2.2 billions are for the pure SLS part and 600 millions for ground equipment\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"tater","CreatedById":119411,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-11-15T18:07:12Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224055416\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022186560\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221636999237\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022208000\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Beccab\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n5 minutes ago, Beccab said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n- The initial four SLS flights to cost 4.1 billions, of which 2.2 billions are for the pure SLS part and 600 millions for ground equipment\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI have to assume the ground includes all testing, refurb, and stacking costs, not physical eqp. Remember that Orion capsules run I think $900M refurbed (?). So some cost is refurb per capsule could easily be 100s of millions.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"AtomicTech","CreatedById":210823,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-11-15T18:26:37Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSimple Solution,\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nUse Superheavy and a discardable specialized upper stage based of Starship with Orion mounted on it.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nEveryone wins!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNASA gets a safer rocket,\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSpaceX gets more money and flexes on Blue Origin,\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nand\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt would look cool.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Beccab","CreatedById":208000,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-11-28T00:46:08Z","Content":"\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedOther\u0022\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed3713486255\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?app=core\u0026amp;module=system\u0026amp;controller=embed\u0026amp;url=https://mobile.twitter.com/DutchSatellites/status/1464729398142066688?t=IvJnTHmriz9j6tZ5fHBBfA%26s=19\u0022 style=\u0022height:314px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nStill an evolving situation, but it\u0027s confirmed\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"JoeSchmuckatelli","CreatedById":154477,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-11-29T16:48:11Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224059830\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022186560\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221638060368\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022208000\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Beccab\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 11/27/2021 at 7:46 PM, Beccab said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedOther\u0022\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed1465800422\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?app=core\u0026amp;module=system\u0026amp;controller=embed\u0026amp;url=https://mobile.twitter.com/DutchSatellites/status/1464729398142066688?t=IvJnTHmriz9j6tZ5fHBBfA%26s=19\u0022 style=\u0022height:356px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nStill an evolving situation, but it\u0027s confirmed\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBE-4 engines or some other?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"tater","CreatedById":119411,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-11-29T17:58:33Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSLS is not changing propellants. Option would be to use one of the other RS-25s, they have several.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"AtomicTech","CreatedById":210823,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-11-29T18:02:27Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224060248\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022186560\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221638208713\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022119411\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022tater\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n3 minutes ago, tater said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSLS is not changing propellants. Option would be to use one of the other RS-25s, they have several.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMan, I wish that somebody else would use the awesome RS-25s for something other than a setback, overdue government jobs program.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"tater","CreatedById":119411,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-11-29T18:12:55Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224060250\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022186560\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221638208947\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022210823\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022AtomicTech\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n10 minutes ago, AtomicTech said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMan, I wish that somebody else would use the awesome RS-25s for something other than a setback, overdue government jobs program.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThey\u0027re too expensive to use on anything else.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"RCgothic","CreatedById":132560,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-11-29T18:26:45Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224060255\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022186560\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221638209575\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022119411\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022tater\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n12 minutes ago, tater said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThey\u0027re too expensive to use on anything else.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThey\u0027re really only good on a sustainer architecture.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThey\u0027re only *really* good on a reusable sustainer architecture.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"tater","CreatedById":119411,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-11-29T18:32:57Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224060259\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022186560\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221638210405\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022132560\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022RCgothic\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n3 minutes ago, RCgothic said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThey\u0027re only *really* good on a reusable sustainer architecture.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnd sadly even that could be marginal. I have not seen detailed data on the RS-25 refurb cost per flight for Shuttle. Comparable new engines, designed for reuse without much work would be the Be-4. If that could be converted to hydrolox, the performance is likely similar to RS-25 as a reality check. Those engines are under $7M each. Any reuse would have to come in with less refurbishing cost than that per engine. If Raptor gets down under a million, then that\u0027s the next point they\u0027d have to hit to be competitive\u2014cheaper than Raptor.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Staticalliam7","CreatedById":216180,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-11-29T18:46:20Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224055443\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022186560\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221637000797\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022210823\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022AtomicTech\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 11/15/2021 at 1:26 PM, AtomicTech said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSimple Solution,\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nUse Superheavy and a discardable specialized upper stage based of Starship with Orion mounted on it.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nEveryone wins!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNASA gets a safer rocket,\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSpaceX gets more money and flexes on Blue Origin,\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nand\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt would look cool.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nproblems:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n1. that\u0027s so cursed\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n2. starship is way wider than orion and would require a ridiculous adaptor\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n3. Starship will\u00A0\u003Cstrong\u003Enever EVER\u00A0\u003C/strong\u003Ebe expended. Period. That just won\u0027t happen.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n4. CURSED\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222021-11-29T18:47:48Z\u0022 title=\u002211/29/2021 06:47  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00222 yr\u0022\u003ENovember 29, 2021\u003C/time\u003E by Staticalliam7\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"RCgothic","CreatedById":132560,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-11-29T18:58:26Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224060267\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022186560\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221638211580\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022216180\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Staticalliam7\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n3 hours ago, Staticalliam7 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nproblems:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n1. that\u0027s so cursed\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n2. starship is way wider than orion and would require a ridiculous adaptor\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n3. Starship will\u00A0\u003Cstrong\u003Enever EVER\u00A0\u003C/strong\u003Ebe expended. Period. That just won\u0027t happen.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n4. CURSED\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSLS is already way wider than Orion and requires a ridiculous adaptor.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nStarship\u0027s only 50cm extra each side.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnd when we say \u0022expendable starship\u0022, really, what we mean is take a stainless steel tube and stick a raptor on the back of it. Knocking together an expendable raptor upper stage would be ridiculously easy.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u0022Starship\u0022 may never be deliberately expended, but it\u0027s not really not difficult to conceive a version with an upper stage for special payloads. 15m diameter payloads. Deep space missions. Things that require launch escape systems. Those sorts of things, even after they\u0027ve got orbital refuelling down\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222021-11-29T22:21:12Z\u0022 title=\u002211/29/2021 10:21  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00222 yr\u0022\u003ENovember 29, 2021\u003C/time\u003E by RCgothic\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"AtomicTech","CreatedById":210823,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-11-29T19:06:50Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nRidiculous Expendable Upper Stage or the REUS\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWith the Adapter Buoyant Launch Expansion or the ABLE.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Beccab","CreatedById":208000,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-11-29T19:22:02Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224060271\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022186560\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221638212306\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022132560\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022RCgothic\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n22 minutes ago, RCgothic said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOrion\u0027s already way wider than SLS and requires a ridiculous adaptor.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nStarship\u0027s only 50cm extra each side.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnd when we say \u0022expendable starship\u0022, really, what we mean is take a stainless steel tube and stick a raptor on the back of it. Knocking together an expendable raptor upper stage would be ridiculously easy.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u0022Starship\u0022 may never be deliberately expended, but it\u0027s not really not difficult to conceive a version with an upper stage for special payloads. 15m diameter payloads. Deep space missions. Things that require launch escape systems. Those sorts of things, even after they\u0027ve got orbital refuelling down\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAlso, it was confirmed that the Superheavy on DearMoon is going to be expended because of the mass required to launch in a TLI without refuelling, so a few Starships being expended wouldn\u0027t be unheard of\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"tater","CreatedById":119411,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-11-29T20:35:06Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224060271\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022186560\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221638212306\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022132560\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022RCgothic\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, RCgothic said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOrion\u0027s already way wider than SLS and requires a ridiculous adaptor.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOrion is 5.03m, and SLS is 8.4m.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nICPS is 5m.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"RCgothic","CreatedById":132560,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-11-29T22:20:43Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224060309\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022186560\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221638218106\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022119411\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022tater\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, tater said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOrion is 5.03m, and SLS is 8.4m.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nICPS is 5m.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI meant it the other way round. (-_-;)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSLS is way wider than Orion. It needs to be adapted down via ICPS, and EUS is needs adapting just as much. For Superheavy it wouldn\u0027t be much more.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222021-11-29T22:21:49Z\u0022 title=\u002211/29/2021 10:21  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00222 yr\u0022\u003ENovember 29, 2021\u003C/time\u003E by RCgothic\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"tater","CreatedById":119411,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-11-29T22:28:25Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224060337\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022186560\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221638224443\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022132560\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022RCgothic\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n7 minutes ago, RCgothic said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI meant it the other way round. (-_-;)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSLS is way wider than Orion. It needs to be adapted down via ICPS, and EUS is needs adapting just as much. For Superheavy it wouldn\u0027t be much more.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nGotcha. It is normal for a crew capsule to be much smaller than the SHLV dia (look at Apollo and N1, the only other examples).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"RCgothic","CreatedById":132560,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-11-29T23:22:49Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224060339\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022186560\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0